<subSubSection id="F34B4C1C61E8C0E356AE8581C7D65B4F" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="way of life">
<paragraph id="094688A2C914DC7F43695681263E7829" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Way of life.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2229ED67E279AB775E892B7AEF771C69" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Size range - 2.8 mm to 4.7 mm; species of this genus not only have color patterns and movements like ants, they have body constrictions, giving them ant-like proportions, even more so than their probable adelphotaxon, 
<taxonomicName id="E7CED22C5B338574667A7AA777ACE89A" authorityName="Laporte de Castelnau" authorityYear="1834" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Calybe" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B5FA1B2622CD7426F2650E0912FFE6D1" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Calybe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. They live near water bodies usually on steep slopes above the water on damp clay soils, in the company of similar-sized ants. They catch small arthropod prey on the run much like tiger beetles. Identification is very difficult without recourse to types; the genus is in need of a taxonomic revision.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="96A8E083F94D65018673954F5D924D3F" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="B7FA5E28F913D3FF0D3106A546E5D837" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A483F72FAD5C388CB59834259AE48A1A" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Southern USA (CA to GA, FL) south to Argentina. Not known from the Caribbean islands.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A47272C162741AAEBB38A8F1B850B3E3" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="notes">
<paragraph id="F408BD58442C6D3E2526D036B6ED1C52" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AE2A7BACDF324C6C6D8D9541AA0CA0A6" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Currently, 17 described species are assigned to this genus, some of which are likely 
<taxonomicName id="017C243D0D6E762997806DCABE3F4F2A" authorityName="Laporte de Castelnau" authorityYear="1834" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Calybe" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="868D93380BAFB4AC18DA18BFD033E725" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Calybe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species; however, many more true 
<taxonomicName id="E65E4A7293FAC06674D03C7E500F9AF5" authorityName="Laporte de Castelnau" authorityYear="1835" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Ega" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E35928AD3C0D52115DBA3CAA3EB547BF" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Ega</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species are represented in the NMNH collection. A taxonomic revision of the group is needed. Identification of species is impossible without recourse to types.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
